For his second Haute Couture collection for Dior, Jonathan Anderson draws inspiration from the expressive work of American sculptor Lynda Benglis, whose artistic journey was profoundly influenced by time spent in Ahmedabad, India. Translating her sculptural language into fashion, the collection embraces tactile craftsmanship through knotting, pleating, moulding, and richly layered textures.
Building on this creative dialogue, Anderson also explores India’s centuries-old artistic traditions, particularly the heritage of chintz textiles and intricate gemstone carving. Celebrating the enduring exchange between Indian craftsmanship and European haute couture, the Fall/Winter 2026–2027 collection reimagines history through a contemporary lens, where art, culture, and exceptional savoir-faire converge.
