For look 29 of his second #Dior Couture collection, #JonathanAnderson revisited #ChristianDior’s 1948 Arizona Coat. The original design was defined by its cocoon-like volume, dramatic wrapped collar, and enveloping silhouette.
@jonathan.anderson reinterpreted it through his own sculptural approach focusing on pleating, knotting, draping, and folding textiles drawing inspiration from the work of sculptor Lynda Benglis.
#RafSimons and #JohnGalliano also reinterpreted the coat. For Fall 2013 Raf remained faithful to the original architecture through his minimalist sensibility. The coat became cleaner and sharper.
